readability_reflection: Concatenation was easier to read as it was building off of something that I am already familiar with.
comprehension_debugging: interpolation was quicker to debug as if you have the {} in the output statement or if there were other formatting errors it was easier to see where in the code that happened.
preference_rationale: I would use concatenation because it required less keyboard inputs and it would be the option I would better understand what it is capable of.
learning_curve: Yes as I have used concatenation before, albeit not often. It allowed me to quickly understand how it would work. On the other hand I have never used interpolation in this way before.
suggestions_improvement: Have the variable name change colors when used with either interpolation or concatenation.
